First Lady Aisha Buhari hosted a special prayer session for the nation. Among other dignitaries in attendance was Mr. Abba Kyari, the Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari, who is currently out of the country on a private visit to the United Kingdom. This was disclosed via a presidential aide’s social media handle. Posting about the event, the aide, Buhari Sallau states that the programme was tagged, ‘The importance of supplications for the nation’s guidance and development.” The event held on Monday (today) at the Banquet Hall, State House, Abuja. See the video, shared by Buhari Sallau via Instagram: